<div class="content" name="RPC_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES" uuid="bc37b8cf-8c94-4804-ad53-0aaf5eaf0ecb"><p>The RPC_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES structure represents security
attributes that can be set through the Remote Procedure Call Protocol
Extensions, as specified in <a href="../ms-cmrp/ba4117c0-530e-4e70-a085-4b4cf5bbf193" data-linktype="relative-path">[MS-CMRP]</a>
section <a href="../ms-cmrp/087e7905-2d56-4c68-8ef1-a4879775579a" data-linktype="relative-path">2.2.3.2</a>.</p><dl>
<dd>
<div><pre> typedef struct _RPC_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES {
   DWORD nLength;
   RPC_SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR RpcSecurityDescriptor;
   BOOLEAN bInheritHandle;
 } RPC_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES,
  *PRPC_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES;
</pre></div>
</dd></dl><p><b>nLength:</b>  The length in bytes of the
security descriptor.</p><p><b>RpcSecurityDescriptor:</b>  The security
descriptor that MUST be as specified in <a href="9729e781-8eb9-441b-82ca-e898f98d29c2" data-linktype="relative-path">RPC_SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR</a>. </p><p><b>bInheritHandle:</b>  <b>TRUE</b> if the
new process inherits the handle; otherwise, <b>FALSE</b>. </p></div>